rComments: She is a talented professor. I had a 3 hour class weekly with her but you don't feel the time pass since her lectures are so interesting and very interactive. She is a professor who really cares about her students so she will go out of her way if you run into any issues. If you have a class with her, take it, you can thank me later.

Loved this class and this prof, she's a real gem. Her assignments if you do what she's asking you'll basically get 100%. Everytime she goes over an assignment she specifies what she's expecting to bump you up from a B to an A. The rubric will get you a B, a small extra will get you an A but she's always very clear on what this is,
Lovely and really wants to connect with students, marks fairly easily, gives you all the tools to succeed.
I loved my class with Professor Crompton. She is dynamic and so helpful. She does talk pretty fast which sometime can be a little overwhelming for second language students. She's awesome
I literally have no idea what I was suppose to learn in this class... But, it's a pretty easy A. Super frustrating though to study for as you literally have no idea what you learned.

Took her class for a minor credit and she is the best! Her teaching style is energetic and witty and funny. She teaches with different learning styles in mind with a mix of lectures, group work, readings and at home videos. I have her class again the following term!
